We consider vaccination in the form of a six month long immunization program. If vaccination is implemented by jurisdiction i, then susceptible individuals move to the recovered class at a rate ωi throughout the entire simulation. We assume that both naturally-acquired and vaccine-derived immunity wane at the same rate ζ. In our model, intervention intensity directly scales the average time to vaccination so that 
